@startuml
title Alternative without Strategy: switch-based matching logic

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho

enum MatchType {
  EXACT
  SUBSTRING
  APPROXIMATE
  REGEX
}

class FilterController {
  - matchType : MatchType
  + matches(searchTerm : String, searchText : String) : boolean
}

FilterController --> MatchType : uses

note right of FilterController
  The matches() method would contain
  a large switch(matchType) statement.

  Adding a new matching algorithm would
  require modifying this core class,
  violating the Open/Closed Principle.
end note

@enduml